Privacy Policy
Information Collection and Usage
At Ziti Creative (ZDC), we prioritize your privacy and comply with all applicable privacy laws. We collect personal information, including names, email addresses, and places of employment, which you provide directly through contact forms or other means. Additionally, we may automatically collect IP addresses and usage data through monitoring tools to enhance your experience on our site. This data helps us communicate with you, provide our services, and tailor our marketing efforts to your interests.
Data Storage, Use, and Sharing
Your personal information is securely stored and used exclusively for our business operations, including service delivery, customer support, and marketing communications. We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. However, we may share your information with trusted service providers who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or serving our users. These service providers are contractually obligated to keep your information confidential and use it only for the specified purposes. We implement stringent security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure, although no system is entirely infallible.
Your Rights and Communication
You have the right to access, correct, amend, or delete your personal data. You can also withdraw your consent for data collection and processing at any time by contacting us. We may communicate with you via email, telephone, text messages, or postal mail for various purposes, including updates, marketing campaigns, and customer service.
To opt-out of such communications or for any questions regarding our privacy practices, please contact us at:
Hello@ziticreative.com